race.comment: Cup time now and SECRET ATTRACTION (11) looks the one to beat after a narrow defeat in the Hannans at Kalgoorlie. Only narrowly beaten there when nothing really went right, but the rise to the mile now is no issue. Rates highly and can go one better now. SENSESSIONAL (2) was in fine form before bumping into Railway Stakes fav Cosmic Crusader at his latest outing. He was best of the rest there however and that holds plenty of weight. Should get every chance from the alley and he's in this up to his ears. Pike opts to ride CAPTAIN PLUTO (4) over SENSESSIONAL and that's worth keeping in mind. He was good first-up from a long way back under the apprentice hoop and he's placed 4/5 second-up. May need some things to go his way but he'll be doing his best work late. PROPHET AND POWER (9) gets in nicely at the weights following his win 8 days ago and he rates highly on that effort. MULTINATIONAL (5) was too strong in the Hannans and will give them something to chase once again.
